===Noun===
{{en-noun}}

# A person who is [[absent]] from his or her [[employment]], [[school]], [[post]], [[duty]], etc.
# {{context|chiefly|British|historical}} A [[landholder]] who lives in another [[district]] or [[country]] than the one in which his [[estate]] is situated.
#* '''1840''', [[w:George_Byron,_6th_Baron_Byron|Lord Byron]], "Letter 374: to Mr. Moore (24 May 1820)," in ''The Works of Lord Byron: With His Letters and Journals, and His Life'', John Murray (London), p. 317:
#*: My trustees are going to lend Earl Blessington sixty thousand pounds (at six per cent.) on a Dublin mortgage.  Only think of my becoming an Irish '''absentee'''!
# One that is nonextistent or lacking.

